The '''High Hill Junction''' is a very fast, efficient, and small but very hard to build junction for special 4-Way direction-crossing.

[[File:en/Community/Junctionary/HighHill.png|none|thumb|450px|High Hill Junction]]
[[File:en/Community/Junctionary/HighHillX.png|none|thumb|400px|Transparency On]]
{{en/Community/Junctionary/Junction Criteria|Expensive|3|1|1|1|1|0|1|1|0|0|1|||
*Handles a very large number of trains at a time.
*Uses special directions
*Small Area needed (10x12) 
*4 Levels (6 tunnels in 3 levels and 2 bridges on top level)
*None or few sharp corners (see improved version for high speed)
*No Deadlocks or Jamming possible
*No Merging or Splitting of the lines
*Handling of single-lines and dual-lines possible. That's the reason no Splits or Merges are used. Do it by your own wishes.
